710109f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue at S. E. corner of 20th Street.
June 25, 1928.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.

710110f-a.text:
Eighth Avenue at S. W. corner of 20th Street.
June 27, 1928.
P.L. Sperr,Photographer.

711564f-a.text:
W. 20th Street, west from a point between Eighth and Ninth Avenues, and across from the latter (E1 thereon). At the left is St. Peter P.E. Church and to the right an apartment home at the N.E. corner of Ninth Avenue. Note the children playing in the street.

June 14, 1938.

P.L. Sperr

711567f-c.text:
(1)
West 20th Street, south side, west from (No.326), but not including Eigth, to and including Ninth Ave. Shown is St. Peter's P.E. Church, Hall and Rectory, at Nos.336-346. Note the Ninth Ave., Elevated Line.

June 20, 1928.
P.L. Sperr.
Neg. 2201

(2)
A limited view of the same, as seen in the opposite direction.
March 12, 1933.

P.L. Sperr.

(3)
A view of the Rectory (No.346), which was erected about 1836-1838.
1914.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
